The paper deals with the online maintenance of a Steiner tree, which is a problem in computational geometry and graph theory. The use of primal-dual framework and global charging argument suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. The study of competitiveness and edge changes also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories. Finally, the use of optimization techniques suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
